description.narrative: UNICEF continued to play a key strategic and convening role with governments and partners, supporting them to translate their commitments on nutrition into policies and actions. Essential components of the KRC2 strategy, including improvement of exclusive breastfeeding practice, improve diet diversity of young children, prevention and treatment of wasting, were mainstreamed into regional and national efforts on nutrition. Adolescent nutrition was re-positioned in the region, with increased awareness of key stakeholders on programmatic gaps and specific needs. These efforts resulted into improved multisectoral enabling environment for nutrition and put the region on track with its commitment on stunting reduction. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/01/2020
